        <div class="section section_with_padding" id="about"> 
            <h2>About me</h2>
            <div class="img_border img_fl"> <a href="#"><img src="images/gallery/NLP.png" alt="image 1" /></a>	
          </div>
            <div class="half right">
                <p>I'm a third year Ph.D. student at Intelligent Systems Program and a Graduate Research Assistant under supervision of Dr. Diane Litman. I do my research in collaboration with Learning Research and development Center (LRDC). My research is on Natural Language Processing, Educational Data, and Tutoring Systems. My current research focus is on Assessing Quality of Writing which is about using Natural Language Processing for Assessing Students' Writing Ability at Scale.</p>
				</div>
            <div class="clear h40"></div>
            <div class="img_border img_fr"> <a href="#"><img src="images/gallery/7.jpg" alt="image 2" /></a>	
          </div>
			<div class="half left">                
            	<p>In my spare time, I enjoy playing music, listening to music, reading books, and watching movies. I play  a Persian musical instrument called setar.</p>
                <p>I am also interested in cultural and social activities. I help the Persian Panthers, Iranian Cultural Association of the University of Pittsburgh, in helding cultural and social events to promote an understanding of Iranian culture and identity </p>
            </div>

